h:722:    sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/promptclaw-daemon.service > /dev/null <<UNIT\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:725:After=network-online.target ollama-0.service promptclaw-datastore.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:726:Wants=ollama-0.service promptclaw-datastore.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:750:    log \"Writing promptclaw-sdp-runner.service...\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:751:    sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/promptclaw-sdp-runner.service > /dev/null <<UNIT\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:754:After=promptclaw-bootstrap.service promptclaw-daemon.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:755:Requires=promptclaw-bootstrap.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:781:    sudo systemctl enable promptclaw-bootstrap.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:782:    sudo systemctl enable promptclaw-daemon.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:783:    sudo systemctl enable promptclaw-sdp-runner.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:784:    ok \"systemd units installed and enabled\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:792:    phase \"12/13 — Starting PromptClaw services\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:795:    sudo systemctl start promptclaw-bootstrap.service\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:799:    sudo systemctl start promptclaw-daemon.service || warn \"Daemon start returned non-zero\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:801:    if systemctl is-active promptclaw-daemon.service &>/dev/null; then\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:808:    sudo systemctl start promptclaw-sdp-runner.service || warn \"SDP runner start returned non-zero\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:810:    if systemctl is-active promptclaw-sdp-runner.service &>/dev/null; then\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:830:    log \"Checking services...\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:832:        if systemctl is-active \"${svc}.service\" &>/dev/null; then\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:840:    if systemctl list-unit-files | grep -q '^ollama-1.service'; then\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:841:        if systemctl is-active ollama-1.service &>/dev/null; then\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:910:        echo \"  - sudo systemctl restart promptclaw-daemon.service\"\n++deploy/r750/install.sh:948:    should_run_phase \"systemd\"    && phase_systemd\n++docs/command-reference.md:103:- child CLI processes spawned by the live daemon run without inherited systemd watchdog variables\n++docs/command-reference.md:151:- `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-bootstrap.service`\n++docs/command-reference.md:152:- `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service`\n++docs/command-reference.md:164:This probe is platform-aware: it checks `launchctl` on macOS homes and `systemctl` on Linux homes so status checks do not crash when the local service manager is absent.\n++docs/command-reference.md:232:- `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now also starts `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service` and launches `observer_vision.py` with `OBSERVER_OLLAMA_URLS=http://127.0.0.1:11435/api/chat,http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/chat`, so the camera summary path uses a dedicated observer queue first and only falls back to the shared local model queue if needed.\n++docs/command-reference.md:234:- `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-av-stack.service` binds that wrapper to `graphical.target` as `User=user`, so the music and face stack can come back after reboot without an operator SSH session.\n++docs/master-plan-20260409.md:60:- ❌ Restart services unless genuinely broken\n++docs/master-plan-20260409.md:87:- Ollama with dual NUMA-pinned systemd units\n++docs/master-plan-20260409.md:90:- Installs all systemd services, starts everything, verifies\n++docs/handoff-protocol.md:27:Before that preflight runs, the launcher now removes a stale `.sdp/run.lock` when it points at a dead PID. That makes routine systemd restarts self-healing instead of leaving the queue runner in a restart loop.\n++docs/handoff-protocol.md:126:- `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` uses `Restart=always` so clean queue-run exits restart automatically; maintenance-gated launcher exits use code `75`, which is marked successful and excluded from restart.\n++docs/handoff-protocol.md:128:For live CypherClaw daemon executions, the transport also records concurrency semaphore transitions (`acquired`, `released`, `rejected`) to Observatory and keeps daemon status probes platform-aware so the same code path can run on macOS launchd and Linux systemd hosts without crashing.\n++docs/handoff-protocol.md:129:The daemon also strips systemd watchdog variables from child-process environments before invoking agents or helper CLIs, so only the daemon main process can send watchdog notifications.\n++docs/handoff-protocol.md:164:There is now a system-level cold-boot handoff for that same stack. `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can call `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` at `graphical.target`, and that wrapper re-establishes the same live invariants the manual recovery used: audio first, then composer, then the meter, then room/sampler backfill if needed, plus explicit face/gallery restarts under X so stale display clients do not survive reboot recovery. That wrapper now also exports the user `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` before launching those display clients, which matters on the live box because SDL/X can stay blank even with `DISPLAY=:0` when the user session runtime dir is missing. It chooses the self-listener backend up front, runs a second delayed dedupe pass so stale late-start copies from other hooks are collapsed back to a single surviving daemon, and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates core AV ownership to that wrapper instead of racing it with its own copies of the same daemons.\n++docs/sdp-cli-stuck-gemini-report.md:35:### systemd Resource Usage\n++docs/sdp-cli-stuck-gemini-report.md:37:When the service was restarted after 7 hours:\n++docs/sdp-cli-stuck-gemini-report.md:66:- **48.6 GB memory consumed** — risked OOM-killing other CypherClaw services\n++docs/sdp-cli-stuck-gemini-report.md:105:# In the systemd unit or in sdp-cli's subprocess invocation\n++docs/sdp-cli-stuck-gemini-report.md:130:- Pipeline: cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service (bash loop launcher)\n++docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md:20:- `sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, and `sampler_dispatch.py`\n++docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md:64:- `sample_capture_daemon.py` can capture and tag room/contact material for\n++docs/architecture.md:106:- systemd-managed runner startup through `my-claw/tools/sdp_runner_launcher.sh`\n++docs/architecture.md:116:Daemon child processes also run with a sanitized environment: `NOTIFY_SOCKET`, `WATCHDOG_PID`, and `WATCHDOG_USEC` are stripped before spawning agent CLIs or helper commands, so only the daemon main process talks to systemd's watchdog socket.\n++docs/architecture.md:118:The managed runner path also repairs a stale `.sdp/run.lock` before preflight runs. That keeps normal systemd restarts from failing their own startup checks after the previous runner PID has been terminated.\n++docs/architecture.md:119:The systemd runner unit itself now uses `Restart=always` so a clean `sdp-cli run` exit cannot silently strand the queue. Maintenance-gated launcher exits stay non-looping through `SuccessExitStatus=75` and `RestartPreventExitStatus=75`.\n++docs/architecture.md:154:Cold boot now has a repo-backed AV entrypoint too. `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` waits for the display, checks whether `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, and only calls `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` if they are still missing. After that it waits for `SuperCollider:out_1`, relaunches `self_listener.py` under a detached session with the explicit verified JACK backend, force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` under X, and exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` for those display clients so they attach to the real user session instead of restarting into a blank SDL/X state. It only backfills `room_listener.py` and `sample_playback_engine.py` if no other startup path has already brought them up during the same boot. If stale copies from earlier bad boot loops are already present, that wrapper now deduplicates those optional daemons back down to one live process, then runs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start copies from another boot hook are also collapsed. That wrapper now also normalizes the live dual-head modes after X recovery, using the observed `DP-2` face screen at `1280x1024` and `DP-0` gallery screen at `3840x2160`, and it launches the face on `:0.0` with the gallery on `:0.1` so the 4K gallery is no longer offset into the wrong coordinate space. `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates core audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample ownership to that wrapper instead of trying to start the same daemons itself. The matching `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` is designed as a system service bound to `graphical.target`, so the live music/face stack can return after reboot even when only the core main daemon unit is already persistent.\n++docs/architecture.md:160:The slow observer summary path is now queue-aware as well. `observer_vision.py` now accepts an ordered `OBSERVER_OLLAMA_URLS` list and the boot path routes it to a dedicated observer queue on `127.0.0.1:11435` before falling back to the shared `11434` instance. A matching `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service` runs that second queue as the `ollama` user against the shared model store, which keeps camera summaries from competing directly with the main local model traffic. When both endpoints are saturated, the observer no longer writes the raw `HTTP Error 503` text as the room description. Instead it publishes a compact local fallback summary derived from the fast image analysis, records `vision_backend` and `vision_error` in `/tmp/observer_state.json`, and backs off before retrying the slow multimodal call again. That keeps the observer state readable during local-model contention while still leaving the slow summary path available when Ollama is free.\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:23:- AGENT_CONTEXT — Identity block prepended to all agent calls with full capabilities list, available services, and 8 active PRDs.\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:32:- `tools/io_guard.sh` — Independent systemd timer (every 30s), kills agents AND sdp-cli at 75% I/O. Sends Telegram alert. Operates independently of the daemon.\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:34:- `tools/server_health.py` — Health checks (disk, memory, load, zombies, daemon, services, temperature). Auto-maintenance: kills stale agents, cleans temp files, truncates oversized logs.\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:37:- OPT-003: Unified auto-recovery service checking all services every 5 min (prd-server-optimization.md)\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:38:- OPT-004: Full boot-resilience — verify all tmpfs dirs, restore DBs, verify services, restart pipeline on boot (prd-server-optimization.md)\n++my-claw/docs/discovery-report.md:57:- `tools/server_health.py` — Periodic health reflection (disk, memory, load, services) with auto-maintenance actions.\n++docs/discovery_20260329_095247.md:158:│       ├── boot_hardening.service  # Systemd unit for boot hardening\n++docs/discovery_20260329_095247.md:173:│       │   ├── systemd/            # Service file for auto-launch\n++docs/discovery_20260329_095247.md:409:**Remote server (CypherClaw) services:**\n++docs/discovery_20260329_095247.md:471:- `systemd/` — Service file for auto-launch on boot\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-av-stack.service:3:After=display-manager.service network-online.target sound.target\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:409:A Python function receives a list of FortiGate firewall rules. Each rule is a dict with keys: id, src, dst, service, action. Write a function that returns all rules where action is \"accept\" and either src or dst contains \"10.10.100.0/24\". Include type hints.\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:413:    {\"id\": 1, \"src\": \"10.10.100.0/24\", \"dst\": \"0.0.0.0/0\", \"service\": \"HTTPS\", \"action\": \"accept\"},\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:414:    {\"id\": 2, \"src\": \"10.10.200.0/24\", \"dst\": \"10.10.100.0/24\", \"service\": \"SSH\", \"action\": \"deny\"},\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:415:    {\"id\": 3, \"src\": \"any\", \"dst\": \"10.10.100.5/32\", \"service\": \"ICMP\", \"action\": \"accept\"},\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:416:    {\"id\": 4, \"src\": \"10.10.100.0/24\", \"dst\": \"10.10.200.0/24\", \"service\": \"ANY\", \"action\": \"deny\"},\n++docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:800:- Are the SD-WAN service rules that reference these members included?\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:105:- `systemctl status ollama` showed `/etc/systemd/system/ollama.service` active since `Fri 2026-03-27 23:29:44 UTC`.\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:109:- `ollama ps` was empty at the final check, so the service is running but no model was currently resident after the benchmark completed.\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:378:**F4 — Systemd Unit Inventory:** The live runtime is service-driven, with tmpfs mounted by systemd and I/O protection on a timer.\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:380:- `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw.service`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:389:- `/etc/systemd/system/io-guard.timer`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:392:  - triggers `/etc/systemd/system/io-guard.service`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:393:- `/etc/systemd/system/io-guard.service`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:396:  - an earlier `systemctl list-units --all` snapshot showed `failed`, so this service has recently changed state\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:413:3. Standardize the runtime Python target for RAG work, then install the vector stack there: either keep using `/usr/bin/python3` for `cypherclaw.service` or move the service to `/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv`, then pull `nomic-embed-text` and install one vector backend in that same interpreter.\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service:3:After=network-online.target ollama.service\n++docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:42:| `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py` | Long-running capture process. Maintains 60-second JACK ring buffers for the contact mic, room mic, and the SuperCollider self bus. Hosts the `InterestingMomentDetector`, the `AcousticFeatures` analyzer, the contextual+acoustic tagger (`build_sample_tags`), the `SampleIndex` SQLite persistence layer, the `save_capture` write path, and the post-song `self_quote()` hook. |\n++docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:43:| `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_verify.py` | Deterministic smoke verifier. Synthesizes a known room sound, drives `save_capture`, and asserts the descriptor lands in `index.sqlite` with the expected context and acoustic tags. Used to sanity-check the capture pipeline without requiring live audio hardware. |\n++docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:64:   at 48 kHz inside `sample_capture_daemon.py`. The\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:83:- The same live daemon toolchain is now portable across the MacBook and Linux server homes, so post-init status and runner checks do not assume one service manager or one repo layout.\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:84:- In the Linux server home, child CLIs launched by the daemon no longer inherit systemd watchdog variables, so helper processes do not generate spurious `Got notification message from PID ...` journal noise.\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:85:- The managed runner now also clears a stale `.sdp/run.lock` before preflight, so normal service restarts do not get stuck behind a dead PID from the previous runner process.\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:141:- For cold boots, the repo now ships `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` plus `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-av-stack.service`. That service is intended to be enabled at `graphical.target` and re-establishes the live AV stack after reboot by calling the hardened audio/composer scripts only when the core stack is still missing, waiting for `SuperCollider:out_1`, relaunching the self-listener on the verified JACK path, force-restarting the face and gallery displays under X with the user runtime dir exported, and deduplicating/backfilling the room listener and sampler so another startup path cannot leave stale late-arriving copies behind. The wrapper now also reapplies the live dual-head geometry after X recovery, keeping the face on `:0.0` / `DP-2` at `1280x1024` and the gallery on `:0.1` / `DP-0` at `3840x2160`. `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates core AV ownership to that wrapper instead of starting overlapping copies of the same daemons itself.\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:144:- The observer path now prefers a dedicated local Ollama queue on `127.0.0.1:11435` through `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service`, with the shared `11434` queue as fallback. If both are saturated, `observer_vision.py` still stays readable instead of surfacing the raw HTTP error: it emits a short local fallback description, records `vision_backend` / `vision_error` in `/tmp/observer_state.json`, and waits before retrying the slow multimodal call.\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-bootstrap.service:4:Before=cypherclaw.service cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service\n++my-claw/scripts/cypherclaw_boot.sh:3:# Run from /etc/rc.local or a systemd service as user\n++my-claw/scripts/cypherclaw_boot.sh:33:ensure_observer_ollama_service() {\n++my-claw/scripts/cypherclaw_boot.sh:34:    sudo -n systemctl start cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service 2>/dev/null || true\n++my-claw/scripts/cypherclaw_boot.sh:81:ensure_observer_ollama_service\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service:3:After=cypherclaw-bootstrap.service cypherclaw.service network-online.target\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service:4:Requires=cypherclaw-bootstrap.service\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:29:- systemd-managed runner hot-looped at 10s intervals, restart counter reached **5007** in ~14 hours\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:30:- `orchestrate` command exited 0 when blocked, making systemd see \"success\"\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:202:The default systemd unit shipped with sdp-cli templates (and used on both CypherClaw and likely CTTickets) executes:\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:212:Update the systemd unit template in the sdp-cli project scaffold:\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:222:And add to the sdp-cli docs: \"For unattended systemd-managed runners, use `sdp-cli run`. Reserve `orchestrate` for interactive use where a human watches the output.\"\n++docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:238:1. **Immediately:** Update default systemd launcher template (trivial, prevents future Bug 1 incidents).\n++docs/coherence-foundations.md:91:- **Governance-as-a-Service (GaaS, Gaurav et al., 2025).** GaaS demonstrates that governance rules can be evaluated as a service layer with 95% precision and 90% recall, without requiring changes to the governed agents. The key insight is separation of concerns: the agent produces output, and a separate system evaluates compliance.\n++docs/coherence-foundations.md:247:- **Rationale:** Reduces infrastructure to a single service\n++my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-image-api.service:4:After=network-online.target cypherclaw-jack.service\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:10:#   1. systemd unit `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` is not active\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:78:# Check 1: systemd unit active\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:80:check_systemd_active() {\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:81:    if systemctl is-active cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service &>/dev/null; then\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:82:        ok \"systemd_inactive\"\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:85:    local state=$(systemctl show -p ActiveState --value cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service 2>/dev/null || echo unknown)\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:86:    alert \"systemd_inactive\" \"cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service is not active (state=${state})\"\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:98:    # The process might be briefly gone between runs — only alert if systemd is also unhappy\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:99:    if ! systemctl is-active cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service &>/dev/null; then\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:100:        alert \"process_missing\" \"No sdp-cli process running and systemd unit not active\"\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:171:# Check 5: systemd hot-loop detection\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:174:    # Count systemd restart events in the last hour\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:177:        restart_count=$(journalctl -u cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service \\\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:192:        \"systemd has restarted cypherclaw-sdp-runner ${restart_count} times in the last hour. Hot-loop detected.\"\n++my-claw/scripts/sdp_watchdog.sh:204:    check_systemd_active || ((failures++))\n++tests/test_healthcheck_script_runtime.py:155:def test_healthcheck_defaults_cover_module_daemon_and_systemd_log(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:365:### 3.1 Main daemon service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:368:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:372:After=network-online.target ollama-0.service ollama-1.service docker-datastore.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:373:Wants=network-online.target ollama-0.service ollama-1.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:404:### 3.2 SDP runner service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:407:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:410:After=cypherclaw-bootstrap.service cypherclaw.service network-online.target\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:411:Requires=cypherclaw-bootstrap.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:441:### 3.3 Web platform service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:444:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-web.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:447:After=network-online.target docker-datastore.service cypherclaw.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:475:### 3.4 Bootstrap service (tmpfs initialization)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:478:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-bootstrap.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:496:### 3.5 Gallery service (GlyphWeave art display)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:499:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-gallery.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:502:After=ollama-0.service cypherclaw.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:503:Wants=ollama-0.service\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:522:### 3.6 Enable all services\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:534:1. docker-datastore.service    → PostgreSQL + Redis containers\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:535:2. ollama-0.service            → NUMA socket 0 (port 11434)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:536:3. ollama-1.service            → NUMA socket 1 (port 11435)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:537:4. ollama-warmup.service       → Preload models into RAM\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:538:5. cypherclaw-bootstrap.service → tmpfs workspace init\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:539:6. cypherclaw.service          → Main daemon (Telegram bot)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:540:7. cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service → SDP task runner\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:541:8. cypherclaw-web.service      → FastAPI dashboard\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:542:9. cypherclaw-gallery.service  → Art display\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:642:2. Stop `cypherclaw.service` on CypherClaw (but keep Ollama + gallery running for art)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:801:| 5 | Create systemd services | Day 10 | Step 4 |\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:803:| 7 | Start services, verify | Day 10 | Step 6 |\n++docs/cypherclaw-emsd-roadmap.md:155:  - key/mode detection and similarity ranking as reusable services\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:612:This installs the `ollama` binary to `/usr/local/bin/ollama` and creates a systemd service. **Disable the default service** — you are going to run two custom ones:\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:641:Create the service file:\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:644:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ollama-0.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:679:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ollama-1.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:836:Create a systemd service for the warmup:\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:839:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ollama-warmup.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:842:After=ollama-0.service ollama-1.service\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:843:Requires=ollama-0.service ollama-1.service\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:874:services:\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:929:> **Note on binding:** Both services bind to `127.0.0.1` only — they are not exposed to the network. Access from other machines should go through Tailscale and an SSH tunnel, or you can later change the bind address to the Tailscale IP (100.x.x.x) if needed.\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:1062:sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/docker-datastore.service << 'UNIT'\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:1065:Requires=docker.service\n++docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:1066:After=docker.service\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1778:### Relevant systemd services\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1780:$ systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"promptclaw|glyphweave|ollama|redis|postgres|chroma|nginx|uvicorn|gunicorn\"\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1781:  nginx.service               loaded active running A high performance web server and a reverse proxy server\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1782:  ollama.service              loaded active running Ollama Service\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1783:  postgresql@16-main.service  loaded active running PostgreSQL Cluster 16-main\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:1784:  redis-server.service        loaded active running Advanced key-value store\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3483:| GW-008 | Create the gallery web server at `tools/art_gallery/` using FastAPI + HTMX + Jinja2 templates. Pages: (1) Gallery grid — all artworks as thumbnails with composite score overlay, filterable by model, art_type, score range, date, pet, theme; sortable by score, date, recency. (2) Artwork detail — full-size render, text version in code block, AEAF player for animations, generation stats (model, effort, time, retries), assessment scores radar chart, qualitative feedback. (3) Experiment dashboard — calibration progress, model leaderboard table, score distributions per model (box plots), generation time comparison, success rate heatmap (model × art_type). (4) Live canvas — prompt input, model/effort/size/palette selectors, generate button, real-time status, result display with scores. (5) Remix — take existing artwork, modify parameters, regenerate. Serve static files (rendered PNGs) from disk. Run as a systemd service on port 8080, accessible via Tailscale. | MUST | T3 | - Gallery grid loads with thumbnail images and scores<br/>- Filtering by model, art_type, score, date works<br/>- Detail page shows PNG, text, scores, generation stats<br/>- AEAF animations play in browser (JS frame player)<br/>- Experiment dashboard shows calibration progress and leaderboard<br/>- Live canvas generates art on demand and displays result<br/>- Remix modifies parameters and regenerates<br/>- Server runs on port 8080 as systemd service |\n++docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3492:| GW-017 | Create a systemd service for the gallery web server at `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-gallery.service`. The service s